<assessmentItem xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1 http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/qti/qtiv2p1/imsqti_v2p1p1.xsd http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML http://www.w3.org/Math/XMLSchema/mathml2/mathml2.xsd" identifier="id656973c0-7590-40e1-be01-e8ce3f79abee" title="anfangswertproblem_homogen_01" adaptive="false" timeDependent="false"><responseDeclaration identifier="RESPONSE_1402045913577" cardinality="single" baseType="string" /><outcomeDeclaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" baseType="float"><defaultValue><value>0</value></defaultValue></outcomeDeclaration><outcomeDeclaration identifier="MAXSCORE" cardinality="single" baseType="float"><defaultValue><value>1</value></defaultValue></outcomeDeclaration><outcomeDeclaration identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC" cardinality="single" baseType="identifier" view="testConstructor"><defaultValue><value>empty</value></defaultValue></outcomeDeclaration><outcomeDeclaration identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" cardinality="multiple" baseType="identifier" view="testConstructor" /><templateDeclaration identifier="a" cardinality="single" baseType="integer" /><templateDeclaration identifier="b" cardinality="single" baseType="integer" /><templateDeclaration identifier="c" cardinality="single" baseType="integer" /><templateProcessing><setTemplateValue identifier="a"><random><multiple><baseValue baseType="integer">-8</baseValue><baseValue baseType="integer">-6</baseValue><baseValue baseType="integer">-4</baseValue><baseValue baseType="integer">-2</baseValue><baseValue baseType="integer">2</baseValue><baseValue baseType="integer">4</baseValue><baseValue baseType="integer">6</baseValue><baseValue baseType="integer">8</baseValue></multiple></random></setTemplateValue><setTemplateValue identifier="b"><randomInteger min="1" max="9" /></setTemplateValue><setTemplateValue identifier="c"><randomInteger min="2" max="9" /></setTemplateValue><setCorrectResponse identifier="RESPONSE_1402045913577"><customOperator definition="VARIABLESTRING" value="-1/($(1)/2*x^2+$(2)*x+$(3))"><variable identifier="a" /><variable identifier="b" /><variable identifier="c" /></customOperator></setCorrectResponse></templateProcessing><itemBody ><p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Wir betrachten die Differentialgleichung \(y'(x)=(<printedVariable identifier="a" />x+<printedVariable identifier="b" />)\cdot y^2(x)\) bzw. in verkürzter Form \(y'=(<printedVariable identifier="a" />x+<printedVariable identifier="b" />)\cdot y^2\).</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Geben Sie die Lösung der Differentialgleichung an, für die \(y(0)=-\frac{1}{<printedVariable identifier="c" />}\) gilt!</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong>Lösung:</strong> \(y(x) =\) <textEntryInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE_1402045913577" class="maxima-formula show-latex" /></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong>Hinweise zur Formeleingabe: </strong>\(x\cdot y\) = <strong>x*y</strong>, \(\frac{x}{y}\) = <strong>x/y</strong>, \(x^y\) = <strong>x^y</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Durch Klicken auf die <strong>?</strong>-Schaltfläche können Sie ihre Formel vor Speichern der Antwort zunächst überprüfen!</span></p></itemBody><responseProcessing><responseCondition><responseIf><customOperator definition="MAXIMA" value="is(equal(ev($(1)),ev($(2))));"><variable identifier="RESPONSE_1402045913577" /><correct identifier="RESPONSE_1402045913577" /></customOperator><setOutcomeValue identifier="SCORE"><sum><variable identifier="SCORE" /><baseValue baseType="float">1</baseValue></sum></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition><responseCondition><responseIf><not><isNull><variable identifier="RESPONSE_1402045913577" /></isNull></not><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC"><baseValue baseType="identifier">incorrect</baseValue></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition><responseCondition><responseIf><and><not><match><variable identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC" /><baseValue baseType="identifier">empty</baseValue></match></not><equal toleranceMode="exact"><variable identifier="SCORE" /><variable identifier="MAXSCORE" /></equal></and><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC"><baseValue baseType="identifier">correct</baseValue></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition><responseCondition><responseIf><and><match><baseValue baseType="identifier">incorrect</baseValue><variable identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC" /></match></and><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL"><multiple><variable identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" /><baseValue baseType="identifier">Feedback1373596027</baseValue></multiple></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition></responseProcessing><modalFeedback  identifier="Feedback1373596027" outcomeIdentifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" showHide="show" title="Musterbeispiel"><p>Wir wollen diejenige Lösung der Dgl. \(y'(x)=(-2x+7)\,y^2(x)\) bestimmen, für die \(y(0)=-\frac13\) gilt.</p><p>Trennung der Veränderlichen und Integrieren beider Seiten liefert</p><p>\(\displaystyle\frac{\mathrm dy}{y^2}=(-2x+7)\,\mathrm dx\iff -\frac1y=-x^2+7x+c\).</p><p>Die allgemeine Lösung hat also die Form \(\displaystyle y(x)=\frac{-1}{-x^2+7x+c}\).</p><p>Da nun \(y(0)=-\frac13\) gelten soll, muss \(c=3\) sein.</p><p><strong>Endergebnis:</strong> \(y(x)=\displaystyle\frac{1}{x^2-7x-3}=\) <strong>1/(x^2-7*x-3)</strong> bzw.<strong> (x^2-7*x-3)^(-1)<br /></strong></p></modalFeedback></assessmentItem>
